    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is attributable to the single-condition nature of ASTM F1717 and is consistent with regulatory precedent. E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; all percent differences within 10% acceptance bound. The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for its intended use in supporting the 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
